  <!-- ===== WHAT IS SADAQAH JARIYAH ===== -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#f8fafb]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6 text-center" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
        What is Sadaqah <span class="text-[#0d9488]">Jariyah?</span>
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
        Unlike regular Sadaqah, Sadaqah Jariyah is <strong>ongoing charity</strong> — an investment whose rewards continue for as long as people benefit, even after you have passed away. It is one of only three deeds that continue to benefit you in the grave.
      </p>

      <!-- Hadith Box -->
      <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-[#0d9488] p-6 rounded-r-xl shadow-sm mb-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-gray-700 italic leading-relaxed text-lg" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
          "When a person dies, their deeds come to an end except for three: ongoing charity (Sadaqah Jariyah), beneficial knowledge, or a righteous child who prays for them."
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#0d9488] font-semibold mt-3 text-sm">— Prophet Muhammad (PBUH), Sahih Muslim</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Benefits Grid -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">
